$interpreted: Soohyeon: Oh right, the fireworks!
Soohyeon: I remember now—fireworks off in the distance! They let off a bright light.
Juan Yun: Look, that's solid proof.
Bull Chieftain: Cut to the chase, boy. What's your point?
Juan Yun: The fireworks that Soohyeon saw were lit by yours truly. And Princess Tindoiimu... well, she was right next to me.
Juan Yun: So I'm your witness.
Juan Yun: How could the princess be with me, and off assassinating General Yu at the same time?
Himawari: And what the heck were you doing lighting fireworks with her in the first place!?
Juan Yun: I just happened to bump into her.
Himawari: But—
Shun: So, our three tribes' most important ceremony, and where was the Qilin Tribe's heir?
Shun: Off lighting fireworks with some insect!? Explain yourself, Juan Yun!
Juan Yun: Well... is it not obvious? Do I really need to say it?
Shun: Out with it, boy!
Juan Yun: Well, compared to a pretty girl... the ceremony falls a little flat.
Juan Yun: Years pass, and the ceremony never changes. Good looks, on the other hand...
Shun: You insolent little...! Spoiled good for nothing...!
Himawari: Hey, lay a finger on my brother-in-law and you'll answer to me!
Maeok: Both of you, please! As I'm sure all of us here are aware, Juan Yun is a boy, and he will act as boys do.
Maeok: This doesn't change the fact that he has presented convincing evidence.
Turtle Chieftain: ......
Wolf Chieftain: ......
Toyokuni: ...Yes, I agree that if Juan Yun is telling the truth, then it would appear Princess Tindoiimu is innocent.
Toyokuni: Indeed, it is possible that the entire Insect Tribe has nothing to do with any of this.
Maeok: I agree.
Maeok: I will call for the immediate release of Princess Tindoiimu from custody, and we will continue the search for General Yu's true killer.
Maeok: Our work here is not—
Shun: No maggot is innocent!
Maeok: General Shun!
Shun: If none of you agree, then the Tiger Tribe will go rip the wings off that butterfly ourselves!
Qing Feng: Why is it that you've begun this hearing without the qilin chieftain?
Maeok: Qing Feng? We thought you weren't...
Qing Feng: Maeok, why are there two representatives from the Kyo Tribe?
Soohyeon: Uncle Qing Feng, my mother is our arbiter, she's neutral!
Qing Feng: Excuse me? Children should be seen and not heard. Your elders are talking.
Qing Feng: Arbiter Maeok, is this how you do things around here?
Soohyeon: But—
Maeok: Soohyeon...
Qing Feng: Likewise, there should not be two here from the Qilin Tribe.
Juan Yun: Dad... you're here...
Qing Feng: And you're here! Under the impression you could represent our tribe?
Juan Yun: No, I just... wanted to help out, and—
Juan Yun: Ugh!
Himawari: Juan Yun!
Qing Feng: You... are a stain on the Qilin Tribe! Rotten fruit from our family tree! Now you come here and disgrace us further!?
Juan Yun: ...Father, please give me a chance... to prove myself...
Qing Feng: A chance? Alright, then.
Qing Feng: The Holy Talisman of the Qilin Tribe is only given to those who can pass through the Waterfall of Illusion. An ancient test.
Juan Yun: Yes, of course...
Qing Feng: But I've never had faith that you could do it.
Qing Feng: Yet you ask for a chance, so... If you can snatch this talisman from my hand, I will accept you as a worthy representative of our tribe.
Juan Yun: Dad, are you serious!?
Qing Feng: I'm serious.
Juan Yun: About Princess Tindoiimu... I overstepped my bounds, trying to prove her innocence.
Qing Feng: You bit off more than you could chew, boy.
Qing Feng: You little...!
Juan Yun: Whew...
Juan Yun: I... I got the talisman!
Juan Yun: You better keep your promise, father!
Juan Yun: The Holy Talisman...!
Qing Feng: Boy! You've no respect for the way things are done!
Juan Yun: You're the one who told me to—
Qing Feng: Forget it! You are far too much like your mother.
Juan Yun: Mom has nothing to do with this! You take that back!
Himawari: Juan Yun!
Qing Feng: Himawari, you are no part of this!
Qing Feng: You can't even take care of yourself—how do you expect to take care of the tribe!?
Qing Feng: Know your limitations, boy.
Qing Feng: Since you can't kneel, then you can lie here and think about what you've done.
Juan Yun: ......
Qing Feng: It's obvious that the Insect Tribe is trying to break up our power. As representative of the Qilin Tribe, I will not allow it.
Maeok: ...Regarding General Yu's death, all present have agreed that the Insect Tribe had nothing to do with it, and—
Qing Feng: Lies! The princess' nanny has already been proven a spy, yet you still think Tindoiimu has nothing to do with this!?
Maeok: O-Of course, it seems a little bit strange, but—
Qing Feng: If you think it's strange, then why the hesitation?
Qing Feng: You all know that the Qilin Tribe, apart from being skilled in the arts of Qimen Dunjia, also creates fine weaponry.
Qing Feng: I propose that—
Bull Chieftain: You wish to make donations?
Qing Feng: —for a fair price, we can provide weaponry for the Alliance armies. And together we can avenge our fallen brother Yu!
Panther Chieftain: Well I'll be! A very generous offer, Qing Feng! Truly more than I could offer...
Panther Chieftain: The Panther Tribe will send our troops, and open our doors to all weary soldiers, for a very reasonable price...
Turtle Chieftain: And a war'd be futile without the Tortoise Tribe's medicinal herbs! With nine years of peace, hell, they'll rot if we don't use em' soon!
Wolf Chieftain: And don't forget the wolve's sturdy armor! If it's for General Yu, we could stand to sell cheaper... We'll even foot the bill if need be!
Shun: Avenge General Yu? Since when have any of them cared about him, or the Tiger Tribe at all for that matter?
Toyokuni: Can't you tell? They don't care... it's just a convenient excuse.
Shun: You mean... maybe the Insect Tribe really didn't murder General Yu?
Toyokuni: Maybe, but I'm afraid that may hardly matter now.
Qing Feng: I think we're all in agreement here. Arbiter Maeok, what is your decision?
Maeok: I... I still think something's not right...
Panther Chieftain: This is what the Panther Tribe wishes. Arbiter Maeok, please make your decision.
Bull Chieftain: The Bull Tribe stands with the qilin. Maeok, please make your final decision.
Turtle Chieftain: Arbiter Maeok, please consider what has ta' be done to bring peace. Make y'er decision.
Wolf Chieftain: Arbiter Maeok, please make your decision.
Seahorse Chieftain: Please make your decision.
Qing Feng: Himawari, you speak for the Leopard Tribe, do you not? What do you say?
Himawari: We... stand with the Qilin Tribe. Arbiter Maeok, please make your decision...
Toyokuni: I fear a unilateral decision will hurt the Alliance's integrity. As such, I stand against all-out war. Arbiter, please make your decision.
Shun: Even if they didn't kill General Yu... the Insects need to be dealt with. Whatever it takes. Arbiter Maeok, please make your decision.
Maeok: ......
Maeok: I understand. Then it pains me to announce that as of now, the peace treaty between the Alliance and the Insect Tribe is...
Maeok: ...officially annulled.
Qing Feng: Maeok, this has been your wisest decision as arbiter to date.
Maeok: ...No, I failed... I couldn't stand up to you... to everyone...
Maeok: ...This wasn't my decision at all...
Juan Yun: Hey Maeok, help me out a second!
Maeok: Ah! Coming!
Juan Yun: Whew... Thank you...
Juan Yun: I never remember how much I need this chair until I don't have it.
Maeok: How can you smile right now? After your dad was so horrible to you...
Maeok: Well...
Maeok: Not just you. He wasn't very nice to me, either.
Juan Yun: ...Hey, Maeok...
Maeok: Yeah?
Juan Yun: My mother didn't approve of war. She was a good person, and I respect her.
Juan Yun: I respect you, too.
Maeok: ......
Maeok: ......
